				<p>&ldquo;There is one virtue, attribute, or principle, which, if cherished and practiced by the Saints, would prove salvation to thousands upon thousands. I allude to charity, or love, from which proceed forgiveness, long suffering, kindness, and patience&rdquo; (Brigham Young, <span class="emphasis">Deseret News,</span> 11 Jan. 1860, 353).</p>
