				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote10-22905_000_032">10.</a>
      </span>
				<p>When real suffering occurs in life, the devil is always there to sour men&rsquo;s hearts in anger, while the Lord continually emanates love. In the same suffering &ldquo;many had become hardened &hellip; and many were softened because of their afflictions&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/62.41?lang=eng#40" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 62:41</a>). What a wonderful example of how to respond to affliction.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-22905_000_032"><a name="-22905_000_032">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote11-22905_000_032">11.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Some destroyers of men&rsquo;s love and peace include but are not limited to: fear, perfectionism, envy, unsubmissiveness, doubt, anger, jealousy, unrighteous control, unbelief, impatience, judging, fostering hurt feelings, pride, contention, murmuring, seeking for honor, competition, lying. All of these are of the natural man, and not of the man of Christ.</p>
			</li>
